}
}
</code></pre> <p> idx = 0          cursorvalues ≥ pivotvalues &lt; pivot </p> <p>So what's happening here?</p> <ul> <li>We pick the first element (<code>idx = 0</code>) of the array as pivot.</li> <li>Index <code>0</code> is omitted from the process.</li> <li>The <code>cursor</code> is where the next element <code>&lt; pivot</code> will be placed.</li> </ul> <p>When the whole loop is done, we are left with <code>cursor</code> pointing to where the next <code>&lt; pivot</code> element would've gone. At this stage we have:</p> <ul> <li><code>idx = 0</code> where pivot is,</li> <li><code>idx = [1, cursor)</code> where elements <code>&lt; pivot</code> are,</li> <li>and <code>idx = [cursor, array.length)</code> where elements <code>≥ pivot</code> are.</li> </ul> <p>So a final swap is needed b/w <code>0</code> and <code>cursor-1</code>. This splits the array in two parts:</p> <ul> <li>\(\big[0, \ cursor\big)\) all \(a_i &lt; pivot\).</li> <li>\(\Big[cursor, \ len(array)\Big)\) all \(a_i \ge pivot\).</li> </ul>

